@papppeter DI work with objects, but this is static, you must use something like this:
~~~
use system\widgets\Pjax;
Pjax::begin();
...
Pjax::end();
~~~

> @papppeter i'm think it's wrong way, because you call `yii\widgets\Pjax::end();`, not `system\widgets\Pjax::end();` or `[get_class($pjaxWidget), 'end']()`

@WinterSilence as long code belongs to the project i accept your answer. 

What if it is a vendor code? I don't have the possibility to change it. (i know i could overwrite it, but that would basically a copy paste of the old code)
